NIGERIAN entrepreneur and social media personality, Happiness Adebayo, popularly known as Mummy Glee has empowered over 100 young entrepreneurs in the country. The event, a maiden edition tagged: “100 Youths Engage Mummy Glee” was recently held at Radisson Hotel, Lagos, and attendees were opportune to have one-on-one interaction with her and some experts of the industry. According to Mummy Glee, she desire to use her life experience to encourage young Nigerians. “I am using this platform to prepared them for any business  challenges they might face in future.  No matter how high unemployment in the Nigeria, they will be succeed.” Thirty outstanding entrepreneurs were able to share their business ideas and ten of them were empowered at the event.